PRIVACY POLICY
Last updated November 07, 2022
Nexvio Inc. ("Company," "we," "us," or "our") provides this privacy notice
for 8mm Vintage Camera ("Application", to explain how and why we might collect,
store, use, and/or share your information when you use our Application as well as
your choices regarding the use of information. By using our Service, you signify
that you have read, understood and agree to our use of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy.
1. HOW WE COLLECT AND USE YOUR INFORMATION
Basically, we do not collect any information or data about our users. As a camera app, 8mm Vintage Camera asks for permission to use the following information that you provide us directly, to implement the Application’s key functionality:
Access to Camera and Microphone – for the Application to record videos and/or take photos.
Access to "Photos" – for the Application to load videos/photos from Storage, add visual effects, and/or make an edited movie.
Location Data – for the Application to save this information to videos/photos, so they might be geotagged. This is an optional permission user may choose to grant.
Third-Party Services
We do NOT use third-party services that may collect and/or analyze your information.
2. SHARE OF YOUR INFORMATION
We do NOT share your information.
3. EMAIL & COMMUNICATION
When you communicate with us with a feedback email, it may include personal information e.g. email address, device model, and version number. We only use this information to contact you and improve our services. We do not share this information with third parties. Nor will this information be used for marketing.
4. CONTACT US
If you have any questions about this PRIVACY POLICY, do not hesitate to contact us at
support@nexvio.com
.